The SEC and a Thumb on the Scale

By Bob Mahalo

The Federal Register was amended again in 2004. 

An interesting note found responding to "Concerns and Opposition" states clearly that Issuers worries about abusive Naked Short Selling was negligible compared to providing efficiency and Reg SHO would handle Naked Shorts. 

20 years later and the efforts to dematerialize stock certificates is nearly complete, with less than 1% of all shares issued being electronic and over 87% owned by Cede & Co. DTCCs nominee. 

Surrendering ownership under the guise of security and efficiency have led companies to the attacks of coordinated hedge fund manipulators such as Andrew Left, recently convicted for these very allegations.
